<span id="freeTextContainer8461283515209793402">Here&apos;s my review: this is book is fucking awesome. <br/><br/>But it&apos;s subtle and indirect so if you&apos;re looking for someone to spoon feed you the &apos;secret secrets&apos; of the universe, it will piss you off.<br/><br/>Best Takeaway: Action isn&apos;t something that you do, it&apos;s more something that does you!<br/><br/>The West is all fucked up about this. We all want what we want so badly, we&apos;re constantly searching for the most direct path to &apos;the thing&apos;. This usually leads to fixation and repetitive cycles of frantic activity and collaps</span>
  <span id="freeText8461283515209793402" style="display:none">Here's my review: this is book is fucking awesome. <br /><br />But it's subtle and indirect so if you're looking for someone to spoon feed you the 'secret secrets' of the universe, it will piss you off.<br /><br />Best Takeaway: Action isn't something that you do, it's more something that does you!<br /><br />The West is all fucked up about this. We all want what we want so badly, we're constantly searching for the most direct path to 'the thing'. This usually leads to fixation and repetitive cycles of frantic activity and collapse. <br /><br />I also know mega successful entrepreneurs that swear by these principles. It's powerful if you can learn a new way to relate to the world beyond your own constant desperate need to control everything and anything.<br /><br />Read it. But maybe instead of reading it, just chill the fuck out and stop trying to make things happen. Go for a walk. Learn a hobby you like. Forget about your goddamn career. And...wait a minute...in that beautiful little silence, something starts moving within you. It lances out like a bolt of purest lightning and there is energy...!...What is this strange new energy...?<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
